            <div type="translation" source="bib:SrinivasaAiyar1946_01">
                <p>
                    Hail! Prosperity! In the ... ... ... ... year of Tribhuvanaccakravartikaḷ Śri
                    Kulōttuṅga Cōla Dēvar: Whereas Kōnāṭṭu Pallavadaraiyan, also called
                    Kai ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ḍaiyan, of Koḍumbāḷūṟ in the Uṟattūr Kūṟṟam of the
                    K(aḍalaḍaiyādilaṅgaiko)ṇḍa cōḻavaḷanāḍu, perished in a strife<supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuḻumi</foreign></supplied> in Periyakuḷam, I, Kunṟan Āḷuḍaiyān, made this endowment of 50 sheep to keep
                    alight a lamp on his behalf. May this be protected by the <foreign>Māhēśvara</foreign>s.                    
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
                <p n="1-2"><gap reason="lost"/> year of the glorious king Kulottuṅga, the emperor of the three worlds.</p>
                <p n="3-4">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">There are</supplied>
                    50 goats that
                    ...
                    gave
                    ...
                    Pallavataraiyaṉ of Kōṉāṭu, alias the lord of <gap reason="lost"/>
                    ...
                    in Koṭumpāḷūr, in the Uṟattūrkūṟṟam, in the <supplied reason="lost">Iraṭṭapāṭi</supplied>koṇṭacōḻavaḷanāṭu.
                </p>
                <p n="4-5"><supplied reason="subaudible">This</supplied> pious donation <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tammam</foreign><note>Sanskrit <foreign>dharma</foreign>.</note></supplied> of the lord Kuṉṟaṉ <supplied reason="subaudible">is under the</supplied> protection of the <foreign>paṉmāheśvarar</foreign>s.</p>
            </div>
            
